## I. HARMONIC FOUNDATION

**Thesis**: The augmented second (A2) and minor third (m3) are enharmonically equivalent in 12-TET (both 3 semitones, frequency ratio ~1.189), yet they inhabit distinct harmonic universes. This composition makes their paradoxical relationship audible.

**Intervals in Question**:
- **Augmented Second**: C→D# (3 semitones) - chromatically raised scale degree, implies dominant/exotic function
- **Minor Third**: C→Eb (3 semitones) - diatonic interval, implies minor tonic stability
- **Vibrational Identity**: Both divide the octave by ~1.189 ratio
- **Contextual Divergence**: One is tension, one is resolution; yet they are the same vibration

